                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>Let me have an early</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Reply—</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Charleston</placeName>\n                <date>July 20 1857</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear Sir/</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Yours of the <date>26<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> Ulto<lb/> came\n                duly to hand as well as the P<lb/> Books. <persName>Abrn<add>?</add>\n                    Moise</persName> desires a state<lb/>-ment of a/c &amp; please send it to me,\n                let<lb/> it be from the beginning, I think he<lb/> owes at least 3 years to\n                    <date>April 1858</date>, he<lb/> will not pay in advance &amp; I have<lb/> to\n                send after its due several times.<lb/> You complain of the ingratitude<lb/> of\n                mankind, I thought you had suf<lb/>ferred so much &amp; so often that you<lb/> had\n                become used to their ingratitude<lb/> &amp; had therefore become a philosopher<lb/>\n                in that respect. Here I must make<lb/> you acquainted with the course of<lb/> the\n                teacher whom I selected for our<lb/> Children &amp; of whom you make<lb/> mention in\n                your last as not having<lb/> ever written you. I <sic>dont</sic> know<lb/> whether\n                it came to your knowledge<lb/> that he was a drunkard, for he<lb/> certainly could\n                not all at once<lb/> or since his sojourn with us, have<lb/> become so, but no less\n                certain it is<lb/> that he indulged in private, &amp; managed</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3sx64w6x/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
