                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>the school committee inquired first into<lb/> the matter as well as the school, &amp;\n                they<lb/> reported the result to the Board of<lb/> Trustees, who summoned\n                    <persName>Mr Cohen</persName> &amp;<lb/> his accusers before them. <persName>Mr\n                    Cohen</persName><lb/> would not appear unless he had in<lb/> writing the charges\n                against him, we<lb/> accommodated him. He appeared &amp; totally<lb/> denied the\n                charge, his accusers ap<lb/>=peared &amp; substantiated the charge by<lb/> others,\n                in addition to which others not<lb/> belonging or connected with the\n                congre<lb/>gation having seen him take at<lb/> one drink in a bar room nearly<lb/> a\n                tumbler of brandy—with these facts<lb/> the board of trustees discharged him<lb/>\n                but submitted their action to the con<lb/>gregation, when they confirmed our\n                action<lb/> The board in their kindness of feeling<lb/> for him ordered a quarters\n                salary to<lb/> be paid him, which would not be<lb/> due him until next\n                    <date>August</date>. The<lb/> gentleman turns away in disappointment<lb/> and\n                sues the congregation for another<lb/> quarters salary which he thinks him<lb/>self\n                entitled to because <hi rend=\"underline\">I</hi> engaged him<lb/> for a year. Now my\n                dear Sir, we<lb/> ought to do good for our kind so that<lb/> we may be repaid in\n                such a manner</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3sx64w6x/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
